                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Robert</forename> of 
                 <surname>the cemetery "de cimiterio"</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_103050">Allerton</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants to the <orgName key="org_103001">monks of Kirkestall</orgName> the whole of his land in <placeName key="place_103122">Colwaynrode</placeName>, 
                  also he quit-claims all his right in all lands, mills, woods, &amp;c. of which the said monks were seised in the
                  year <origDate when="1238">1238</origDate>, viz. in the territories of <placeName key="place_103050">Allerton</placeName>,
                  <placeName key="place_103200">Hedingleid</placeName>
                        <!-- SIC in Turner and Coxe: must be an error somewhere for Hedingleia -->, and <placeName key="place_103303">Osmundthorp</placeName>. 
                  Witn. <persName>
                           <forename>Alan</forename>, vicar of <placeName role="vicar" key="place_103253">Ledes</placeName>
                        </persName>
                  . </p>
